CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1959, page 8, reads: "Charlene's First Birthday - Little Charlene Marietta Foggie, daughter of the Rev. and Mrs. Charles H. Foggie, of Wesley Centre AME Zion Church, poses for a picture with her grandparents on the occasion of her first birthday, Jan. 5. Mr. and Mrs. James L. Foggie Sr. came from Boston to be with their newest grandchild on her natal day and shared the festivities which included a family dinner party with all the dainty frills, which was hosted by the baby's parents. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Reverend Charles H. Foggie holding his daughter, Charlene Foggie Barnett in light colored dress and hair bow, on her first birthday standing inside the parsonage of Wesley Center AME Zion Church
